<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-04 01:58 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0771 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-HKN-KINGS-LBPT     09-04 0313
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-KINGS-LBPT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KINGS SET FOR CAMP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGER PHILLIPS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Beginning at 7 this morning, Kings players are scheduled to
report for medical examinations, the first step in the process that
will lead to Sunday's start of training camp, next Saturday's
exhibition opener and the beginning of the regular season in
Nashville in 28 days.
</P>
<P>
   Nearly 55 players are scheduled to compete for jobs at training
camp, but several of those expected on hand may not be around at
the start, and several others definitely won't be.
</P>
<P>
   General Manager Dave Taylor announced Friday that problems with
visa paperwork are delaying the arrival of Finnish defenseman Jere
Karalahti.
</P>
<P>
   But Taylor said that even though Karalahti's past includes an
addiction to heroin, he does not foresee the rookie's arrival being
significantly delayed.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't think it's a major issue,'' Taylor said. ``We think
it's a formality. We're not exactly sure of the time frame, but we
hope to have him here sometime next week.''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, forwards Glen Murray and Jason Podollan, and
defenseman Mattias Norstrom remain unsigned.
</P>
<P>
   Taylor said the players probably won't be permitted to skate
with the team unless they are close to an agreement.
</P>
<P>
   Additionally - and what would a Kings season be without
injuries? the casualty list already is at three.
</P>
<P>
   Defenseman Philippe Boucher, who had foot surgery at the end of
last season, still isn't 100 percent, though the Kings are hoping
he will be by the end of camp. Rookie center Scott Barney will miss
all of training camp and won't be ready for the start of the season
because of a back injury. Another rookie center, Eric Belanger, is
sidelined indefinitely after surgery this week to remove a rib that
was causing a circulatory disorder.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-04-99 0158EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
