   Some worry, too, that Giuliani, a likely U.S. Senate candidate,
who relishes the opportunity to express his views on civic duty and
the law among other topics, might use the case to make a political
statement.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Hamlin believes politics played a role in both sides'
decision to pick the mayor as foreman. ``The plaintiff's lawyers
imagine that he feels he needs to make friends in Harlem,'' said
Ms. Hamlin. ``The people who work for the landlord think he is a
conservative and he would want to prevent lots of suits like
this.''
</P>
<P>
   Whether Ms. Hamlin is right and whether Giuliani adds to or
detracts from the process _ all will be revealed this week.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-04-99 1202EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
