   PRO FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   COXNET NFL FOOTBALL PREVIEW SECTION 0905
</P>
<P>
   CoxNet has prepared a four-page football preview section. The
ready-to-use pages are available now and can be obtained via the
Budget Tool or through Locations of the AJC Database. The section
can also be found on the Cox Server in the sports folder. Here is a
budget for the pages:
</P>
<P>
   PAGE 1: TARGETING THE QUARTERBACKS - NFL quarterbacks have
become an endangered species. Rushing the quarterback is at a
premium, and blitzes have become an integral part of nearly every
team's defensive package. And it's no longer just defensive linemen
running down the quarterback. Linebackers, cornerbacks and safeties
are flying into backfields as well. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes color photos of 4 quarterbacks
and 1 linebacker.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: SEASON PREDICTION -If the theme of the 1999 Minnesota
Vikings were put on a Web site, it would be called
Atlanta-or-bust.com. Here's why the Vikings will spend Jan. 30 in
the Georgia Dome. They should get in their reservations now -
avoiding the millennium rush - for Super Bowl XXXIV. (Cantu, Austin
American-Statesman) Art includes 1-column color photo of Viking
Randy Moss and 2 color button logos of Broncos and Vikings.
</P>
