Gramatica hopes to make his experience in the NFL a family
tradition. (Eichelberger, N.Y. Times News Service) Art includes
1-column color photo of kicker.
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY
</P>
<P>
   HKN-THRASERSSTART _ ORLANDO, Fla. _ Now, they are like every
other NHL team. No more mock expansion drafts, no more
choreographed jersey unveilings, no more blur of breakfasts with
men's clubs from the local church and synagogue. The Thrashers are
just another a hockey team in search of an identity, a roster and a
power play as 65 players take the ice for the beginning of training
camp. ``I guess this is the climax to what we've been building the
last 13, 14 months,'' said the team's general manager and chief
architect, Don Waddell. ``We're two years old at this point, but
we're getting ready to kick off our second life.'' The first
regular-season game is Oct. 2 against New Jersey at Philips Arena.
(Schultz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   w/HKN-THRASHERS-KNOW _ ATLANTA _ Fred Shero _ the late coach of
the Philadelphia's ``Broad Street Bullies''_ once defined his
hockey philosophy as follows: ``Take the shortest route to the puck
and arrive in ill humor.'' If Shero's words give some clue as to
hockey's nature, it still doesn't fully define what separates the
sport from those concluding with ``ball'' _ as in baseball,
football, basketball. Therefore, as a primer for the NHL's return
to Atlanta, we offer a list of 10 things that make hockey
different. Led by ice, of course. (Schultz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   HKN-WHATHOCKEY _ ATLANTA _ Need to get up-to-date on the NHL?
Here are some things to remember. (Schultz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
