<P>
   TECH-FAIRFAX _TYSON'S CORNER, Va. _ The pastures and orchards
that not long ago produced a wealth of food here are sprouting a
new bounty now: high-tech jobs, stock options, luxury subdivisions
and cars, cars, cars. All over the rolling parcels of green in
Fairfax County southwest of Washington, entrepreneurs are raising
the heavily wired, glass-encased office buildings that will contain
the industrial base for the Information Age. How this once boring,
bucolic community figured out the future, and then made a fortune
from it, is a lesson in post-urban infrastructure. (Geewax, Cox
News Service)
