<P>
   CONGRESS _ WASHINGTON _ When lawmakers returns to Capitol Hill
this week they will face a host of controversial issues that could
have a major impact on Atlanta and the rest of the state. For
example, Republicans want to cut $1.6 billion from HUD's budget,
which would mean a loss of $9 million in housing funds for Atlanta
and additional $30 million for the state. Outside of the annual
appropriations battle, Congress is expected to deal with Rep.
Charlie Norwood's contentious proposal to overhaul managed care. In
the wake of the Atlanta shootings, they are also expected to take
up legislation that would regulate gun sales. (Carr, Cox News
Service) MOVED
