 UNDATED: than fair.'' 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEVILS
</P>
<P>
   Among the Missing
</P>
<P>
   Patrik Elias and Brendan Morrison were missing _ along with
notable acquisitions from other teams _ when the Devils reported
for their physicals Saturday in West Orange, N.J. The two are
restricted free agents, and as of Saturday morning, they had not
come to an agreement with the team.
</P>
<P>
   Morrison, a rookie-of-the-year candidate last season, has
practiced with a group of other members of the team in informal
workouts for the last month, and he is closer to signing a contract
than Elias, who has been in his native Czech Republic for most of
the summer.
</P>
<P>
   Morrison made a base salary of $450,000 last year, but bonuses
brought that figure to $800,000. He is seeking a contract similar
to that of Bill Muckalt, his former teammate at Michigan, who
recently signed with Vancouver for $2.9 million for three years.
Morrison finished second in scoring among rookies last year with 10
more points that Muckalt.
</P>
<P>
   The Devils' other restricted free agents during the summer have
been signed, with Jason Arnott the last one to come to terms.
Arnott agreed to a new one-year contract on Friday and reported
with 56 others officially on the training camp roster.
</P>
<P>
   _ ALEX YANNIS
</P>
</TEXT>
