-- A soldier's monument, part of the 15-year nocturnal
grave-robbing collection of Anthony Casamassima, 40. Casamassima's
testimony helped convict Alastair Duncan, a leading authority on
Tiffany stained glass, on charges of dealing in stolen mausoleum
art. Casamassima is awaiting sentencing on a variety of charges,
including trafficking in stolen property. Duncan, who is appealing
his conviction, is to be sentenced on Oct. 27 and is facing up to
35 years in prison. (Jeffery A. Salter/New York Times Photo)
</P>
