Mo. _ For more than two decades, Rachel Cooke of Louisburg, Kan.,
told almost no one the full story of her troubled childhood. But
now, on the day she will attend the Barry Manilow concert at
Sandstone Amphitheatre, she doesn't care who knows _ especially the
singer. After all, she said, his music saved her life.
